    "_note": "HyperLiquid Bridge2 (Arbitrum mainnet, 0x2df1c51e09aecf9cacb7bc98cb1742757f163df7). batchedDepositWithPermit takes an ARRAY of deposits; each element moves `usd` (uint64, USDC 6-dp) of USDC (0xaf88d065e77c8cC2239327C5EDb3A432268e5831) from `user` to the bridge. We map each element to a USDC transfer-to-Bridge2 intent via array_emit -> Multicall of token/erc20_transfer (token = USDC literal, recipient = $to = the Bridge2 contract, amount = $inputs.[1] = usd). On the calldata path the tuple elements decode POSITIONALLY so per-element fields are $inputs.[0]=user, [1]=usd, [2]=deadline, [3]=signature (signature unused by the body). usd is uint64 but alloy widens to a U256 word, so the amount renders faithfully. The per-element `user` is the depositor; erc20_transfer has no `from` field (the actor is the signer), so `user` is informational only.",
